{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Making custom templates isn’t too complicated, and after reading this page you should be able to easily create templates for all your needs. If you create a template that you think many users would find useful, feel free to open a PR at "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler-templates"},{"type":"text","text":" to add it to the default set of templates."}]},{"anchor":"Creating-a-custom-template","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Creating a custom template"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a new template ‘repository’ (a directory that will contain a collection of templates)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a directory inside the template repository. The name of the directory is the name of your template. ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" is a reserved name, and the directory must not start with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"."},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Template.toml"},{"type":"text","text":" file (inside the template directory) with the following contents:"}]}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"toml","code":["description = \"My first package template.\"","platforms = [\"macOS\", \"Linux\"] # Adjust according to your needs, valid values are `macOS` and `Linux` (for the future)"]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add files to the template (see below for details)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any files within the template directory (excluding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Template.toml"},{"type":"text","text":") are copied to the output directory when creating a package. Any occurrence of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{{PACKAGE}}"},{"type":"text","text":" within the file’s relative path is replaced with the package’s name. Any occurrence of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{{PACKAGE}}"},{"type":"text","text":" within the contents of files ending with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".template"},{"type":"text","text":" is replaced with the package’s name and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".template"},{"type":"text","text":" file extension is removed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All indentation must be tabs (not spaces) so that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"create"},{"type":"text","text":" command’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--indentation"},{"type":"text","text":" option functions correctly."}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also create a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" directory within the template repository. Whenever creating a new package, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" directory is applied first and should contain the common files between all templates, such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".gitignore"},{"type":"text","text":" file. A template can override files in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" template by containing files of the same name."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the swift-bundler-templates repository"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler-templates","overridingTitle":"the swift-bundler-templates repository"},{"type":"text","text":" for some example templates."}]},{"anchor":"Using-a-custom-template","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Using a custom template"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"sh","code":["swift bundler create MyApp --template MyTemplate --template-repository \/path\/to\/TemplateRepository"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftbundler\/custom-templates"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftBundler\/documentation\/SwiftBundler\/custom-templates","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom templates are a great way to tailor Swift Bundler to your workflow."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Custom templates","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftBundler"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftBundler\/documentation\/SwiftBundler"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Advanced usage","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftBundler\/documentation\/SwiftBundler\/metal-shaders"],"generated":true}],"references":{"https://github.com/stackotter/swift-bundler-templates":{"title":"the swift-bundler-templates repository","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the swift-bundler-templates repository"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler-templates","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-bundler-templates"},"doc://SwiftBundler/documentation/SwiftBundler":{"role":"collection","title":"SwiftBundler","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create macOS apps with Swift packages instead of Xcode projects."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftBundler\/documentation\/SwiftBundler","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftbundler"},"doc://SwiftBundler/documentation/SwiftBundler/metal-shaders":{"role":"article","title":"Metal shaders","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Metal shaders with Swift Bundler."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftBundler\/documentation\/SwiftBundler\/metal-shaders","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftbundler\/metal-shaders"}}}